definition.value: A glycosylgalactose consisting of a beta-D-galactofuranose residue and a D-galactofuranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->5) glycosidic bond.
A trans-2-enoyl-CoA that is the S-sinapoyl derivative of coenzyme A.
A long-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of stearic acid.
A glycosyl alditol consisting of alpha-L-fucopyranosyl and N-acetyl-D-glucosaminitol residues joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
An amino disaccharide that consists of N-acetyl-D-glucosamine having a 3-sulfated N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl residue attached at position 4.
An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of thiophene-2-carboxylic acid.
The S-vinylacetyl derivative of coenzyme A.
